title: Indian-Spiced Lentils and Lamb
summary: Indian-Spiced Lentils and Lamb might be just the main course you are searching for. This gluten free recipe serves 4 and costs $2.05 per serving. One serving contains 389 calories, 23g of protein, and 15g of fat. This recipe is liked by 1 foodies and cooks. A mixture of ground lamb, canned tomatoes, carrot, and a handful of other ingredients are all it takes to make this recipe so flavorful. To use up the olive oil you could follow this main course with the Sauteed Banana, Granolan and Yogurt Parfait as a dessert. From preparation to the plate, this recipe takes roughly 1 hour and 10 minutes. All things considered, we decided this recipe deserves a spoonacular score of 61%. This score is solid. Try Indian Spiced Lentils, Indian Spiced Lentils – 5 Points, and Indian-spiced Mushrooms And Lentils for similar recipes.
instructions: Heat a saucepan over medium-high heat. Add oil to pan; swirl. Add lamb and next 4 ingredients (through red pepper); saut 4 minutes, stirring to crumble. Add onion, carrot, and jalapeo; saut 4 minutes or until lamb is browned. Add garlic; saut 1 minute, stirring constantly. Stir in tomato paste; saut 30 seconds.                                                                                                 Add lentils; saut 30 seconds. Stir in broth and next 3 ingredients (through tomatoes); bring to a boil. Reduce heat, and simmer for 40 minutes or until lentils are tender. Ladle about 1 cup lentil mixture into each of 4 bowls; top each serving with 1 tablespoon yogurt and 1 tablespoon cilantro.
